race.comment: Going with FRENCH SOUL (7) who looks to have a fair bit of upside. Well in the market on debut on the Synthetic at Devonport and after getting back found the line nicely for third. Shapes as though the extra ground will suit and may well appreciate the turf. Follow up. SURF SOUL (5) is nearing a win, the latest racing on speed here over 1200m and boxing on for fourth. Keeps improving and should be in the finish. VORTISTAR (8) was well supported second-up and pushed forward from a wide gate before fading to finish seventh. Has the ability and best figures stack up but drawn even wider today so will need a good steer from the claimer. FAVOURITE DEPUTY (6) was in the market and got home late on debut. With the claim and run under the belt should be in the finish. NATALDI (14) found the 1100m too sharp fresh but fitter again and the extra trip looks a big plus.
